From: David Woodhouse <dwmw@amazon.co.uk>
Date: Fri, 19 Jan 2018 13:48:28 +0100
Subject: x86/cpufeatures: Add Intel feature bits for Speculation Control
Git-repo: git://git.infradead.org/users/dwmw2/linux-retpoline.git
Git-commit: 61d61da25ebe44b483dbff5eaa44e87676af1399
Patch-mainline: Queued in subsystem maintainer repository
References: bsc#1068032 CVE-2017-5715

Add three feature bits exposed by new microcode on Intel CPUs for
speculation control. We would now be up to five bits in CPUID(7).RDX
so take them out of the 'scattered' features and make a proper word
for them instead as that leaf is a pure feature bits leaf.

